Quote: Mr. J. A. Perano, head of the famous Tory Channel whaling party, and who was recently injured in an encounter with a fighting whale, was the central figure in a unique broadcasting arrangement last night, when from his bed in Picton Hospital he spoke over the radio telephone direct to the British Broadcasting Corporation in London, giving a brief history of the Tory Channel whaling industry and referring to some of the more notable adventures of his party and its predecessors in the pursuit of whales.
